SLO       <p><hi type="bold">I-V. Henohova Prispodoba o prihodnjem deležu hudobnih in pravičnih</hi></p>
ENG       <p><hi type="bold">I-V. Parable of Enoch on the Future Lot of the Wicked and the Righteous.</hi></p>

SLO       <title>Poglavje 1</title>
ENG       <title>Chapter 1</title>

SLO         <hi type="super">1</hi> Besede Henohovega blagoslova, s katerimi je blagoslovil izvoljene ╓in╖ pravične, ki bodo živeli v dnevu stiske, ko bodo vsi hudobni ╓in brezbožni╖ odstranjeni.<opomba>(Prim. 5 Mz 33,1 'Mojzesov blagoslov.')</opomba><r r="Deut.33.1">5 Mz 33,1</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">1</hi> The words of the blessing of Enoch, wherewith he blessed the elect ╓and╖ righteous, who will be living in the day of tribulation, when all the wicked ╓and godless╖ are to be removed.<opomba>(Cf. Deut. xxxiii. 1, ' the blessing of Moses.')</opomba><r r="Deut.33.1">Deut 33:1</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">2</hi> In prevzel je svojo prispodobo<r r="Num.24.3-Num.24.4">4 Mz 24,3-4</r> ter rekel – Henoh, pravičen mož, čigar oči je Bog odprl, je videl videnje Svetega v nebesih, ┌ki┐ so mi ga pokazali angeli, in od katerih sem slišal vse, in od njih sem razumel, kar sem videl, a ne za ta rod, temveč za oddaljen rod, ki bo prišel.
ENG         <hi type="super">2</hi> And he took up his parable<r r="Num.24.3-Num.24.4">Num 24:3-4</r> and said—Enoch a righteous man, whose eyes were opened by God, saw the vision of the Holy One in the heavens, ┌which┐ the angels showed me, and from them I heard everything, and from them I understood as I saw, but not for this generation, but for a remote one which is for to come.

SLO         <hi type="super">3</hi> Glede izvoljenih sem rekel, in prevzel ┌svojo┐ prispodobo glede njih:
ENG         <hi type="super">3</hi> Concerning the elect I said, and took up ┌my┐ parable concerning them:

