SLO       <title>Poglavje 2</title>
ENG       <title>Chapter 2</title>

SLO         <hi type="super">1</hi> <opomba>(V ii-v. 3 red narave je v nasprotju z neurejenostjo človekovega sveta. V Neftálijevi oporoki iii. 2, 3 je ljudem rečeno, naj spoštujejo Božji zakon, tako kot sonce, luna in zvezde spoštujejo svoj določen red. Stražarji, ki so zapustili svoj naravni red, pa so označeni kot opozorilo. Prim. Sirah xvi. 26-28, Pss. Sol. xviii. 12-14.)</opomba> Opazujte vse, kar se dogaja na nebu, kako ne spreminjajo svojih orbit ┌in┐ svetila, ki so na nebu, kako vsa vstajajo in zahajajo v vrstnem redu vsakega v svojem obdobju in ne kršijo svojega določenega reda.
ENG         <hi type="super">1</hi> <opomba>(In ii-v. 3 the order of nature is contrasted with the disorder of man’s world. In Test. Naph. iii. 2, 3, men are told to observe God's law as sun, moon, and stars observe their appointed order, and the Watchers who left their natural order are held up as a warning. Cf. Sirach xvi. 26-28, Pss. Sol. xviii. 12-14.)</opomba> Observe ye everything that takes place in the heaven, how they do not change their orbits, ┌and┐ the luminaries which are in the heaven, how they all rise and set in order each in its season, and transgress not against their appointed order.

SLO         <hi type="super">2</hi> Glejte zemljo in pazite na stvari, ki se dogajajo na njej od prve do zadnje, ┌kako trdne so┐, kako se ┌nobena od stvari na zemlji┐ ne spreminja, ┌ampak┐ se ┌vam┐ prikažejo vsa Božja dela.
ENG         <hi type="super">2</hi> Behold ye the earth, and give heed to the things which take place upon it from first to last, ┌how steadfast they are┐, how ┌none of the things upon earth┐ change, ┌but┐ all the works of God appear ┌to you┐.

SLO         <hi type="super">3</hi> Glejte poletje in zimo,<opomba>([Hebrejščina ima samo dva letna časa. Poletje in zimo. Prim. 1 Mz viii. 22, Iz xviii. 6, Zah xiv. 8.])</opomba><r r="Gen.7.22">1 Mz 7,22</r><r r="Isa.18.6">Iz 18,6</r><r r="Zech.14.8">Zah 14,8</r> ╓kako je celotna zemlja nasičena z vodo, in oblaki, rosa in dež ležijo na njej╖.
ENG         <hi type="super">3</hi> Behold the summer and the winter,<opomba>([The Hebrews had two seasons only. Summer and Winter. Cf. Gen. viii. 22, Isa. xviii. 6, Zech. xiv. 8.])</opomba><r r="Gen.7.22">Gen 7:22</r><r r="Isa.18.6">Isa 18:6</r><r r="Zech.14.8">Zech 14:8</r> ╓how the whole earth is filled with water, and clouds and dew and rain lie upon it╖.

