ENG         <hi type="super">5</hi> (I saw the spirits of the children of men who were dead, and their voice went forth to heaven and made suit.)E (I saw ˱the spirit of˲ a dead man making suit, and his voice went forth to heaven and made suit.)Gg<opomba>(5-7. Formerly thought to describe the first division of Sheol, which contains the souls of the righteous, who in their life were persecuted, and suffered a violent and undeserved death. The idea of the righteous or of the angels crying for vengeance on the wicked occurs in all the sections of Enoch. Cf. ix. 1-3, 10, 11, xxii. 5-8, xlvii. 1, 2, lxxxix. 76, xcvii. 3, 5, xcix. 3, 16, civ. 3. Cf. also Rev. vi. 10; 4 Ezra iv. 35. But really these verses describe not a division of Sheol, but the sight of a soul demanding vengeance.)</opomba><r r="Rev.6.10">Rev 6:10</r>

