SLO       <p><hi type="bold">LXVII. Božja obljuba Noetu. Kraji kaznovanja angelov in kraljev.</hi></p>
ENG       <p><hi type="bold">LXVII. God’s Promise to Noah: Places of Punishment of the Angels and of the Kings.</hi></p>

SLO       <title>Poglavje 67</title>
ENG       <title>Chapter 67</title>

SLO         <hi type="super">1</hi> V tistih dneh mi je prišla beseda od Boga in rekel mi je: »Noe, tvoj delež je prišel gor pred Mene, delež brez krivde, delež ljubezni in poštenosti.<r r="Gen.6.9">1 Mz 6,9</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">1</hi> And in those days the word of God came unto me, and He said unto me: ‘Noah, thy lot has come up before Me, a lot without blame, a lot of love and uprightness.<r r="Gen.6.9">Gen 6:9</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">2</hi> In zdaj angeli delajo leseno (zgradbo) in ko bodo opravili to nalogo, bom Svojo roko položil nanjo in jo ohranim, in iz nje bo vzklilo seme življenja in nastopila bo sprememba, tako da zemlja ne bo ostala brez prebivalca.<opomba>(V lxxxix. 1, Noe sam naredi barko.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">2</hi> And now the angels are making a wooden (building), and when they have completed that task I will place My hand upon it and preserve it, and there shall come forth from it the seed of life, and a change shall set in so that the earth will not remain without inhabitant.<opomba>(In lxxxix. 1, Noah himself makes the ark.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">3</hi> Tvoje seme pa bom utrdil pred seboj na veke vekov in razširil bom tiste, ki prebivajo s teboj. Ne bo nerodovitno na obličju zemlje, ampak bo blagoslovljeno in na zemlji se bo množilo v Gospodarjevem imenu.«
ENG         <hi type="super">3</hi> And I will make fast thy seed before me for ever and ever, and I will spread abroad those who dwell with thee: it shall not be unfruitful on the face of the earth, but it shall be blessed and multiply on the earth in the name of the Lord.’

SLO         <hi type="super">4</hi> In On bo zaprl tiste angele, ki so pokazali nepravičnost, v tisto gorečo dolino, ki mi jo je poprej pokazal moj ded Henoh, na zahodu<opomba>(izposojeno iz lii. 1. Povečuje geografsko zmedo.)</opomba> med gorami iz zlata, srebra, železa, mehke kovine in kositra.<opomba>(LXVII. 4 – LXIX. 1. Ta del obravnava kazen padlih angelov. Značilne poteze druge sodbe so tu prenesene na prvo, kraji, ki se razlikujejo v prispodobah, pa so tu zamešani, npr. goreča dolina Gehene je postavljena med kovinske gore (lxvii. 4), medtem ko je v liv. 1 na 'drugem delu zemlje'. 4. Potop in sodba padlih angelov sta tukaj omenjena skupaj kot v x. 2, 4, toda tukaj (1) je zapor goreča dolina (= Gehena iz  liv) čeprav je tam ognjena peč, ki sprejme angele) in (2) to je predhodni zapor, ne končni.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">4</hi> And He will imprison those angels, who have shown unrighteousness, in that burning valley which my grandfather Enoch had formerly shown to me in the west<opomba>(borrowed from lii. 1. It increases the geographical confusion.)</opomba> among the mountains of gold and silver and iron and soft metal and tin.<opomba>(LXVII. 4 – LXIX. 1. This section deals with the fallen angels' punishment. Characteristic features of the second judgement are here transferred to the first, and localities distinct in the parables are here confused, e.g. the burning valley of Gehenna is placed among the metal mountains (lxvii. 4), while in liv. 1 it is in 'another part of the earth'. 4. The Deluge and the judgement of the fallen angels are mentioned together here as in x. 2, 4, but here (1) the prison is the burning valley (= the Gehenna of liv, though there it is a furnace of fire that receives the angels), and (2) this is the preliminary prison, not the final.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">5</hi> Videl sem tisto dolino, v kateri je bil velik nimir in nemir vodá.<opomba>(5, 6. Značilnosti potopa in vulkanskih motenj so združene, slednje so povezane s kaznijo angelov.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">5</hi> And I saw that valley in which there was a great convulsion and a convulsion of the waters.<opomba>(5, 6. Features of the Deluge, and volcanic disturbances are combined, the latter connected with the angels' punishment.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">6</hi> Ko se je vse to zgodilo, je iz te ognjene staljene kovine in od nemira na tistem mestu nastal vonj po žveplu in to je bilo povezano s tistimi vodami. In tista dolina angelov, ki so zavedli (človeštvo), je gorela pod tisto deželo.<opomba>(Verjeli so, da pod dolino Gehene obstaja podzemni ogenj. Prim. xxvii. 1 (opomba). Primerjaj tudi z usodo Sodome.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">6</hi> And when all this took place, from that fiery molten metal and from the convulsion thereof in that place, there was produced a smell of sulphur, and it was connected with those waters, and that valley of the angels who had led astray (mankind) burned beneath that land.<opomba>(A subterranean fire was believed to exist under the Gehenna valley. Cf. xxvii. 1 (note). Cf. too the fate of Sodom.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">7</hi> Skozi njene doline tečejo ognjeni tokovi, kjer so kaznovani ti angeli, ki so zavedli tiste, ki prebivajo na zemlji.<r r="Rev.3.10">[Raz 3,10]</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">7</hi> And through its valleys proceed streams of fire, where these angels are punished who had led astray those who dwell upon the earth.<r r="Rev.3.10">[Rev 3:10]</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">8</hi> Toda te vode bodo v tistih dneh<opomba>(pisateljevih.)</opomba> služile kraljem, mogočnim in vzvišenim in tistim, ki prebivajo na zemlji, za ozdravljenje telesa, toda za kaznovanje duha;<opomba>(tj. na končni sodbi.)</opomba> torej njihov duh je poln poželenja, da bi bili lahko kaznovani v svojem telesu,<opomba>(Trenutno greh njihovega duha vključuje samo trpljenje telesa, ki ga ozdravi voda, toda v Geheni bosta trpela tako duh kot telo.)</opomba> kajti zatajili so Gospodarja Duhov in vsak dan vidijo svojo kazen,<opomba>(lahko preberejo svoje bodoče muke v sedanjih mukah angelov.)</opomba> a kljub temu ne verjamejo v Njegovo ime.<opomba>(Topli vrelci so posledica srečanja vode in ognja pod zemljo, s katerim so bili kaznovani angeli. Herod Veliki se je zatekel k takemu izviru, Callirrhoe, vzhodno od Mrtvega morja, Joseph. Ant. xvii. 6, 5. Prim. topli vrelci Machaerus, Joseph. Bell. Iud. vii. 6. 3.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">8</hi> But those waters shall in those days<opomba>(those of the writer.)</opomba> serve for the kings and the mighty and the exalted, and those who dwell on the earth, for the healing of the body, but for the punishment of the spirit;<opomba>(i.e. in the final judgement.)</opomba> now their spirit is full of lust, that they may be punished in their body,<opomba>(At present the sin of their spirit entails suffering on the body only, which is healed by the waters, but in Gehenna spirit and body alike will suffer.)</opomba> for they have denied the Lord of Spirits and see their punishment daily,<opomba>(i.e. can read their future torments in the present ones of the angels.)</opomba> and yet believe not in His name.<opomba>(The hot springs result from the meeting of the water and fire underground by which the angels were punished. Herod the Great resorted to such a spring, Callirhoe to the east of the Dead Sea, Joseph. Ant. xvii. 6, 5. Cf. the hot springs of Machaerus, Joseph. Bell. Iud. vii. 6. 3.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">9</hi> V skladu s tem kakor postane gorenje njihovih teles hudo, se bo ustrezna sprememba zgodila v njihovem duhu na veke vekov; kajti pred Gospodarjem Duhov nihče ne bo izrekel prazne besede.<opomba>(Kralji se bodo pokesali pod mukami, a brez uspeha.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">9</hi> And in proportion as the burning of their bodies becomes severe, a corresponding change shall take place in their spirit for ever and ever; for before the Lord of Spirits none shall utter an idle word.<opomba>(The kings will repent under torment, but without avail.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">10</hi> Kajti nadnje bo prišla sodba, ker verjamejo v poželenje svojih teles in zanikajo Gospodarja Duhov.<opomba>(Ta stavek je edinstven v Henohu.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">10</hi> For the judgement shall come upon them, because they believe in the lust of their body and deny the Spirit of the Lord.<opomba>(This phrase is unique in Enoch.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">11</hi> Te iste vode bodo v tistih dneh doživele spremembo; kajti ko so ti angeli kaznovani v teh vodah, bodo ti vodni izviri spremenili svojo temperaturo in ko se bodo angeli povzpeli, se bo ta voda iz izvirov spremenila in postala hladna.<opomba>(Z angelovim odhodom se vode ohladijo. Prim. Origen, c. Celsum v. 52.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">11</hi> And those same waters will undergo a change in those days; for when those angels are punished in these waters, these water-springs shall change their temperature, and when the angels ascend, this water of the springs shall change and become cold.<opomba>(With the angel's departure the waters cool. Cf. Origen, c. Celsum v. 52.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">12</hi> Zaslišal sem Mihaela odgovoriti in reči: »Ta sodba, s katero so sojeni angeli, je pričevanje za kralje in mogočne, ki posedujejo zemljo.«
ENG         <hi type="super">12</hi> And I heard Michael answering and saying: ‘This judgement wherewith the angels are judged is a testimony for the kings and the mighty who possess the earth.’

SLO         <hi type="super">13</hi> Ker te vode sodbe služijo za ozdravljenje teles kraljev in poželenju njihovega telesa; zato ne bodo videli in ne bodo verjeli, da se bodo te vode spremenile in postale ogenj, ki večno gori.<opomba>(Vode zdaj zdravijo in njihova zdravilna moč zaslepi kralje za ogenj spodaj, ki je prihranjen za njihove prihodnje muke. Prim. v. 8.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">13</hi> Because these waters of judgement minister to the healing of the body of the kings and the lust of their body; therefore they will not see and will not believe that those waters will change and become a fire which burns for ever.<opomba>(The waters heal now, and their healing virtue blinds the kings to the fire below which is reserved for their future torment. Cf. v. 8.)</opomba>

