SLO       <p><hi type="bold">LXVIII. Mihael in Rafael sta bila presenečena nad strogostjo sodbe.</hi></p>
ENG       <p><hi type="bold">LXVIII. Michael and Raphael astonied at the Severity of the Judgement.</hi></p>

SLO       <title>Poglavje 68</title>
ENG       <title>Chapter 68</title>

SLO         <hi type="super">1</hi> Potem, ko mi je moj ded Henoh dal učenje o vseh skrivnostih v Knjigi Prispodob, ki mu je bila dana, jih je zame zbral v besedah Knjige Prispodob.<opomba>(Upoštevajte, da Prispodobe že obstajajo kot popolno delo v rokah urednika, ki priznava, da jih je združil z Noetovimi odlomki. Pomen tega poglavja še zdaleč ni jasen.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">1</hi> And after that my grandfather Enoch gave me the teaching of all the secrets in the book in the Parables which had been given to him, and he put them together for me in the words of the book of the Parables.<opomba>(Note that the Parables already exist as a complete work in the hands of the redactor, who confesses to combining them with the Noah fragments. The meaning of this chapter is far from clear.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">2</hi> Tisti dan je Mihael odgovoril Rafaelu in rekel: »Moč duha me prenaša in mi povzroča, da se tresem zaradi strogosti sodbe skrivnosti, sodbe angelom. Kdo lahko vzdrži strogo sodbo,<opomba>(Morda kazen za skrivnosti, ki so jih razkrili Satani.)</opomba> ki je bila izvršena, in pred katero so se stopili?«<opomba>(Ta dialog med Mihaelom in Rafaelom razkriva strogost sodbe nad padlimi angeli ali bolje rečeno Satani.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">2</hi> And on that day Michael answered Raphael and said: ‘The power of the spirit transports and makes me to tremble because of the severity of the judgement of the secrets,<opomba>(Perhaps the penalty for the secrets divulged by the Satans.)</opomba> the judgement of the angels: who can endure the severe judgement which has been executed, and before which they melt away?’<opomba>(This dialogue of Michael and Raphael sets forth the severity of the judgement over the fallen angels, or rather the Satans.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">3</hi> Mihael je spet odgovoril in Rafaelu rekel: »Kdo je tisti, čigar srce se ne omehča glede tega in čigar vajeti niso vznemirjene zaradi te besede sodbe, (ki) je prišla nanje zaradi tistih, ki so jih tako zavedli?«<opomba>(tj., Satani, ki so zapeljali te angele.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">3</hi> And Michael answered again, and said to Raphael: ‘Who is he whose heart is not softened concerning it, and whose reins are not troubled by this word of judgement (that) has gone forth upon them because of those who have thus led them out?’<opomba>(i. e. the Satans who seduced these angels.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">4</hi> In zgodilo se je, ko je stal pred Gospodarjem Duhov, da je Mihael takole rekel Rafaelu: »Z njimi ne bom sodeloval pod Gospodarjevim očesom; kajti Gospodar Duhov je bil jezen nanje, ker počno, kakor bi bili oni Gospodar.<r r="Isa.14.11-Isa.14.13">Iz 14:11-13</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">4</hi> And it came to pass when he stood before the Lord of Spirits, Michael said thus to Raphael: ‘I will not take their part under the eye of the Lord; for the Lord of Spirits has been angry with them because they do as if they were the Lord.<r r="Isa.14.11-Isa.14.13">Iz 14:11-13</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">5</hi> Zato bo vse, kar je skrito, prišlo nanje na veke vekov, kajti niti angel niti človek ne bosta imela svojega deleža (v njej), ampak so samo oni prejeli svojo sodbo na veke vekov.<opomba>(ne angel ne človek ne trpita njihovih muk, ampak ti padli angeli sami.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">5</hi> Therefore all that is hidden shall come upon them for ever and ever; for neither angel nor man shall have his portion (in it), but alone they have received their judgement for ever and ever.’<opomba>(neither angel nor man suffers their torments, but these fallen angels alone.)</opomba>

