ENG         <hi type="super">27</hi> And I saw till all the wolves who pursued those sheep perished and were drowned.

SLO       <p><hi type="bold">LXXXIX. 28-40. Izrael v puščavi, dajanje postave, vhod v Palestino.</hi></p>
ENG       <p><hi type="bold">LXXXIX. 28-40. Israel in the Desert, the Giving of the Law, the Entrance into Palestine.</hi></p>

SLO         <hi type="super">28</hi> Toda ovce so pobegnile od tiste vode in šle naprej v divjino, kjer ni bilo vode in nobene trave. Začele so odpirati svoje oči<opomba>(tj. da si povrnejo svoj duhovni vid in se vrnejo k Bogu. Prim. lxxxix. 32, 33, 41, 44, 54, xc. 6, 9, 10, 35.)</opomba> in videti. Zagledal sem Gospodarja ovc kako jih pase in jim daje vodo in travo in da je tista ovca šla in jih vodila.<opomba>(28-40. Potovanje po divjini, postava na Sinaju in okupacija Palestine.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">28</hi> But the sheep escaped from that water and went forth into a wilderness, where there was no water and no grass; and they began to open their eyes<opomba>(i.e. to recover their spiritual vision and return to God. Cf. lxxxix. 32, 33, 41, 44, 54, xc. 6, 9, 10, 35.)</opomba> and to see; and I saw the Lord of the sheep pasturing them and giving them water and grass, and that sheep going and leading them.<opomba>(28-40. Journeyings through the wilderness, the lawgiving on Sinai, and the occupation of Palestine.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">29</hi> Tista ovca se je povzpela na vrh te vzvišene skale in Gospodar ovc jim jo je poslal.<opomba>(Mojzes se povzpne na Sinaj in se vrne v Izrael. 2 Mz xix.)</opomba><r r="Exod.19.1-Exod.19.25">2 Mz 19:1-25</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">29</hi> And that sheep ascended to the summit of that lofty rock, and the Lord of the sheep sent it to them.<opomba>(Moses ascends Sinai, and returns to Israel. Exod. xix.)</opomba><r r="Exod.19.1-Exod.19.25">2 Mz 19:1-25</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">30</hi> Potem sem videl Gospodarja ovc, ki je stal pred njimi in Njegov videz je bil velik, grozen in veličasten, in vse tiste ovce so ga videle in bile prestrašene pred Njegovim obrazom.
ENG         <hi type="super">30</hi> And after that I saw the Lord of the sheep who stood before them, and His appearance was great and terrible and majestic, and all those sheep saw Him and were afraid before His face.

SLO         <hi type="super">31</hi> Vse so se bale in trepetale zaradi Njega in klicale so k tisti ovci z njimi,<opomba>(= Aron.)</opomba> [ki je bila med njimi]: »Nismo sposobne stati pred našim Gospodarjem ali ga gledati.«
ENG         <hi type="super">31</hi> And they all feared and trembled because of Him, and they cried to that sheep with them<opomba>(= Aaron.)</opomba> [which was amongst them]: ‘We are not able to stand before our Lord or to behold Him.’

SLO         <hi type="super">32</hi> Tista ovca, ki jih je vodila, se je ponovno povzpela na vrh te skale, toda ovce so postale zaslepljene in zašle iz poti, ki jim jo je pokazal, toda tista ovca ni vedela o tem.<r r="Exod.24.12-Exod.24.18">2 Mz 24:12-18</r><r r="Exod.32.1-Exod.32.35">2 Mz 32:1-35</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">32</hi> And that sheep which led them again ascended to the summit of that rock, but the sheep began to be blinded and to wander from the way which he had showed them, but that sheep wot not thereof.<r r="Exod.24.12-Exod.24.18">2 Mz 24:12-18</r><r r="Exod.32.1-Exod.32.35">2 Mz 32:1-35</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">33</hi> Gospodar ovc je bil silno jezen nad njimi in tista ovca je to odkrila, se spustila z vrha skale, prišla do ovc in našla večino izmed njih zaslepljenih in odpadlih.
