SLO         <hi type="super">34</hi> Ko so jo<opomba>(tj. Mojzesa.)</opomba> zagledale, so se bale in trepetale ob njeni prisotnosti in se želele vrniti k svojim stajam.<opomba>(= opustile svoje napake.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">34</hi> And when they saw it<opomba>(i.e. Moses.)</opomba> they feared and trembled at its presence, and desired to return to their folds.<opomba>(= give up their errors.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">35</hi> In tista ovca je s seboj vzela drugo ovco in prišla do tistih ovc, ki so odpadle in jih začela klati. Ovce so se bale njene prisotnosti in tako je ta ovca pripeljala nazaj tiste ovce, ki so odpadle in vrnile so se v svoje staje.<r r="Exod.32.26-Exod.32.35">2 Mz 32:26-35</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">35</hi> And that sheep took other sheep with it, and came to those sheep which had fallen away, and began to slay them; and the sheep feared its presence, and thus that sheep brought back those sheep that had fallen away, and they returned to their folds.<r r="Exod.32.26-Exod.32.35">2 Mz 32:26-35</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">36</hi> Videl sem v tej viziji, dokler tista ovca ni postala mož in zgradila hišo za Gospodarja ovc in vse ovce namestila v tisto hišo.<opomba>(tj. naredili šotorsko svetišče za središče svojega bogoslužja.)</opomba><opomba>(Mojzes postane mož, da zgradi šotorsko svetišče. Prim. vrstici 1, 9.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">36</hi> And I saw in this vision till that sheep became a man and built a house for the Lord of the sheep, and placed all the sheep in that house.<opomba>(i.e. made the tabernacle the centre of their worship.)</opomba><opomba>(Moses becomes a man to build the tabernacle. Cf. verses 1, 9.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">37</hi> Videl sem, dokler ta ovca, ki je srečala tisto ovco, ki jih je vodila, ni zaspala. Videl sem, dokler niso bile vse velike ovce pogubljene in so na njihovem mestu vstale majhne ter prišle na pašnik in se približale toku vode.<opomba>(Jordan s pašnikom vzhodno od njega.)</opomba><opomba>(Smrt Arona in vsega rodu, ki je izšel iz Egipta.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">37</hi> And I saw till this sheep which had met that sheep which led them fell asleep: and I saw till all the great sheep perished and little ones arose in their place, and they came to a pasture, and approached a stream of water.<opomba>(Jordan with a pasture to the east of it.)</opomba><opomba>(Death of Aaron and of all the generation that had gone out of Egypt.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">38</hi> Potem se je tiste ovca, njihov vodja, ki je postal človek, umaknila od njih in zaspala in vse ovce so jo iskale in nad njo jokale z velikim jokom.<opomba>(Mojzes umre. Prim. 5 Mz xxxiv.)</opomba><r r="Deut.34.1-Deut.34.12">5 Mz 34:1-12</r>
ENG         <hi type="super">38</hi> Then that sheep, their leader which had become a man, withdrew from them and fell asleep, and all the sheep sought it and cried over it with a great crying.<opomba>(Moses dies. Cf. Deut. xxxiv.)</opomba><r r="Deut.34.1-Deut.34.12">5 Mz 34:1-12</r>

SLO         <hi type="super">39</hi> Videl sem, dokler niso prenehale jokati za tisto ovco in prešle ta vodni tok, in tam sta se vzdignili dve ovci kot vodji namesto tistih <dodano>[dveh]</dodano>, ki sta jih vodili in zaspali (db. »sta zaspali in jih vodili«).<opomba>(Jozue in Kaleb. Popravljam kuellomu = 'vse' v kel'ehomu = 'obe'.)</opomba>
ENG         <hi type="super">39</hi> And I saw till they left off crying for that sheep and crossed that stream of water, and there arose the two sheep as leaders in the place of those which had led them and fallen asleep (lit. ‘had fallen asleep and led them’).<opomba>(Joshua and Caleb. I emend kuellomu = 'all' to kel'ehomu = 'the two'.)</opomba>

SLO         <hi type="super">40</hi> Videl sem, dokler niso ovce prišle na lep kraj in v prijetno in veličastno deželo in videl sem, dokler tiste ovce niso bile zadovoljne; in tista hiša je stala med njimi v prijetni deželi.<opomba>(Palestina. Prim. Dan xi. 16, 41.)</opomba><r r="Dan.11.16">Dan 11,16</r><r r="Dan.11.41">Dan 11,41</r>
